                            <comment id="12921696" author="stack" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 14:23:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you have a patch Andy to post?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921857" author="andychen" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2010 14:57:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;add patch&lt;br/&gt;
BTW, tihs path uses PriorityBlockingQueue instead of LinkedBlockingQueue as compactionQueue&apos;s data structure (this is an experimental method, we want to compact regions that have most storefiles first)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12925240" author="andychen" created="Wed, 27 Oct 2010 03:03:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;two modifications:&lt;br/&gt;
1. interrupt compaction threads immediately when region server shutdown&lt;br/&gt;
2. disable ThreadPoolExecutor automatically adjust the pool size, that means fix compaction thread number&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
